column5: Went to a local trib today, got there late and only got to fish an hour. went 1/2. The one i lost being a half rotting salmon that i was too digusted to touch. Here it is ( the bow i landed, lol)  Also the first bow on my new 14" Raven and Islander
Nice fish, and diggin' that background.  Is that a wallpaper mural or something?
Nice photo, that's an amazing background shot.  Scary how good photo manipulation has gotten...  Mike
Weedman: its just a image I found on google images, search river or something like that and theres lots
Gotta love them Arizona trout.  Good job!
Nice fish and picture.  Is that a san juan worm or just a tiny pinky?? It looks extremely thin for a 3"
Nice fish anr luv the back round W2G on the fish    jordan
That's it, you've convinced me to go out and catch my first Steelie - hope the gf doesn't mind me buying a new rod!  Thanks for the report!  UF
Hey, did you tie that jig yourself with the stuff you bought from Bass Pro?
Did you use Vertius Fluid mask for the image extraction? I love the edges...very nice. Oh, yeah...nice fish too.
Dude nice Fish!!! and nice photoshopping as well!!  Thats Fantastically Sweet!  Gerritt.
Nice job, congrats on the bow.  Hope you like the new set up.  JP
Rick i used photshop cs2, and i did it by hand with the eraser tool, does the best job IMO
